reviews.text: This is a really beautiful old church. It's kind of sad that it isn't used anymore as a church. I found it fascinating that there seems to be burial chambers under the entire floor. And a copy of Rembrandt's and Saskia's marriage record on display.

We weren't allowed in, because there was some exhibition. We wanted to see the church nothing more. The exhibition cost 10 euros, to my mind it doesn't worth this money. We managed to see many pictures of this exhibition and they weren't beautiful at all. I recommend to see it when there is no any exhibition.

You have to give a church 4 stars. The sheer effort of building it deserves that. Even if it is a bit dour.... grim might be a better word. Or perhaps austere... You can decide. Its not unmissable. You'll enjoy the other sights of Amsterdam if you miss this. It won't change your life if you do go. You might feel a bit colder. Or wish you'd been in a cafe.. Or a bar.. I don't know. You do. I went and explored it. I shan't feel the need to do so again.

Amsterdam by night at its finest! There’s something magical about this place - I had to be there during a red moon that made it even more special. But from any angel this place is simply beautiful - do not miss it.

Cool church. Plays a Chime I believe at the top of every hour. Looks awesome over the skyline. All of Amsterdam is beautiful. Next to red light district and next to a lot of bars and food when your ready to do other things
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

Nice museum in a beautiful and calm part of the city. Employees are kind and helpful. The museum is not flashy or innovative in the set-up, nor is it very big. The entrance fee however is quite low and all the information that is accessible, is good. So the price quality is fine. Take about two hours to stroll easily through the museum and spend the rest of the day enjoying the beauty that is the city of Maastricht.
Small yet very educative on geological history. Great for kids as well!
Nice museum to visit. Many details about nature including extinct and exist animals, big and small sizes. They also have temporary exhibition, it was about insect photography when I went.
Small but interesting museum, however most info provided in Dutch only

Small museum, but certainly a must see in the town. In a cozy atmosphere you could enjoy a nice collection within permanent, temporary exhibitions and outside. 
The specialty of museum is ancient animals found very close by to Maastricht - mammoths and dinos. 
It is a nice visit for both children and adults. Small souvenir shop is available.
